gomodel:SYNGO_5179  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Figure 2c: Cultured hippocampal neurons were immunostained for endogenous SynDIG1, SAP102 (DLG3), vGlut1, GluA2 (GRIA2), vGAT and gephyrin. SynDIG1 partially co-localized with excitatory, but not inhibitory, synaptic marker proteins. Postsynaptic localization for SynDIG1 was apparent in surface-SynDIG1 co-stainings with PSD95 and vGlut1 (Fig. S4b) in dissociated rat hippocampal neurons transfected at 4DIV.\n\nFigure S4c: SynDIG1 and PSD95 are co-enriched in various PSD biochemical fractions prepared from mouse P14 brain.\n\nFigure 8: Immunostaining for SynDIG1 and MAP2 in dissociated rat hippocampal neurons at 10 DIV showed clear dendritic puncta.\n\nFigure 3: SynDIG1 interacts with GluA2 in heterologous cells.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: Supplementary Figure S4 legend: \"(B) SynDIG1 is present at the surface of excitatory synapses in dissociated neurons. Dissociated rat hippocampal neurons were transfected at 4 days in vitro (DIV) with a SynDIG1 construct with an HA-tag at the C-terminus (SynDIG1-HA). At 8 DIV, neurons were live-labeled with anti-HA antibodies (red) to label surface HA epitopes and subsequently fixed and stained with anti-PSD95 (green) anti-vGlut1 (blue) antibodies to label synapses.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"Anti-SynDIG1 mAb L42/17 was generated using standard procedures (Bekele-Arcuri et al., 1996) from a Balb/c mouse immunized with a GST fusion protein containing amino acids 1-183 of mouse SynDIG1.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5179" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

